1
00:00:23,490 --> 00:00:25,981
For unexplainable reasons

2
00:00:26,360 --> 00:00:28,162
my son Ken-ichi and l

3
00:00:28,162 --> 00:00:30,221
have been estranged for 10 years.

4
00:00:32,066 --> 00:00:35,035
There is a profound chasm between us

5
00:00:36,136 --> 00:00:38,105
which hurts me deeply.

6
00:00:38,105 --> 00:00:41,438
I want us to be close again.

7
00:00:43,210 --> 00:00:46,847
I have learned that

8
00:00:46,847 --> 00:00:50,146
Ken-ichi is in the hospital.

9
00:00:51,118 --> 00:00:54,554
His wife Rie has asked me to visit him.

10
00:00:55,022 --> 00:00:55,647
She has suggested to me

11
00:00:56,423 --> 00:00:57,856
that it would be an opportunity

12
00:00:59,326 --> 00:01:05,231
for Ken-ichi and I to speak to each other

13
00:01:07,234 --> 00:01:14,163
and to improve our relationship.

14
00:01:14,608 --> 00:01:16,337
Hence I have come to Tokyo.

15
00:01:25,085 --> 00:01:28,486
You must be surprised at the changes

16
00:01:30,057 --> 00:01:31,991
in Tokyo over the past 10 years.

17
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:44,967
Ken-ichi has been unwell for awhile.

18
00:01:46,573 --> 00:01:48,404
He's suffering from stomach pain.

19
00:01:49,042 --> 00:01:51,602
It often disturbs him at night.

20
00:01:54,114 --> 00:01:58,608
He hasn't been diagnosed yet.

21
00:02:07,628 --> 00:02:09,152
Excuse me.

22
00:02:09,463 --> 00:02:11,988
Give me a moment.

23
00:02:13,367 --> 00:02:16,598
I'll tell Ken-ichi you're here.

24
00:02:18,272 --> 00:02:23,437
He doesn't know that you've come.

25
00:02:44,598 --> 00:02:45,997
Father is here to see you.

26
00:02:46,500 --> 00:02:47,660
Why don't you let him in?

27
00:02:48,368 --> 00:02:50,996
He's come a long way to see you.

28
00:02:52,005 --> 00:02:54,098
Why should I see him?

29
00:02:54,975 --> 00:02:56,340
Who asked him to come?

30
00:02:57,077 --> 00:02:58,408
Did you?

31
00:02:58,612 --> 00:03:00,409
I never said I wanted to see him.

32
00:03:01,381 --> 00:03:03,144
Please don't talk like this.

33
00:03:05,352 --> 00:03:08,014
Enough, I don't want to see him.

34
00:03:30,210 --> 00:03:31,472
Father.

35
00:03:34,214 --> 00:03:35,704
Please wait.

36
00:03:43,624 --> 00:03:45,216
Father

37
00:03:45,626 --> 00:03:50,427
he's sick and in great pain.

38
00:03:51,665 --> 00:03:54,759
Don't take his words to heart.

39
00:03:55,469 --> 00:03:57,232
Forgive him.

40
00:03:57,638 --> 00:04:00,835
Let me talk to him.

41
00:04:14,054 --> 00:04:15,453
This tape

42
00:04:18,191 --> 00:04:20,284
was made by Ken-ichi in China.

43
00:04:23,196 --> 00:04:27,292
It was broadcast as part of a TV special.

44
00:04:29,570 --> 00:04:32,539
Please have a look at his work.

45
00:04:38,445 --> 00:04:40,379
Make sure you watch it.

46
00:04:41,448 --> 00:04:43,279
Please.

47
00:04:56,897 --> 00:04:59,866
Mr. Takata, it's ready.

48
00:05:06,573 --> 00:05:09,176
Thank you. Would you like a drink?

49
00:05:09,176 --> 00:05:11,111
No, thank you.

50
00:05:11,111 --> 00:05:12,738
I have another appointment.

51
00:05:13,580 --> 00:05:15,275
Do you know how-to use a VCR?

52
00:05:15,449 --> 00:05:16,541
Yes.

53
00:05:44,678 --> 00:05:47,704
Let me introduce

54
00:05:48,148 --> 00:05:50,446
an expert in oriental folk arts

55
00:05:50,751 --> 00:05:53,914
Mr. Ken-ichi Takata.

56
00:05:54,354 --> 00:05:56,914
He is widely published on the subject.

57
00:05:57,457 --> 00:05:58,947
We have some footage

58
00:05:59,860 --> 00:06:01,327
shot by Mr. Ken-ichi of a mask opera.

59
00:06:13,607 --> 00:06:16,872
This opera originates from Yunnan Province.

60
00:06:30,424 --> 00:06:32,654
This is Mr. Ken-ichi Takata

61
00:06:32,959 --> 00:06:34,461
from the faculty of Oriental Folk Arts

62
00:06:34,461 --> 00:06:35,723
at the University of Tokyo.

63
00:06:36,430 --> 00:06:37,731
He's here to see you perform.

64
00:06:37,731 --> 00:06:38,699
Thank you.

65
00:06:38,699 --> 00:06:40,633
This is Mr. Li Jiamin.

66
00:06:41,201 --> 00:06:42,725
He's our lead singer.

67
00:06:43,470 --> 00:06:45,335
This is amazing.

68
00:06:45,772 --> 00:06:47,433
You are incredible.

69
00:06:47,708 --> 00:06:48,367
He says you are incredible.

70
00:06:48,642 --> 00:06:50,769
I could be better. I have a cold today.

71
00:06:51,278 --> 00:06:52,506
Come back and I'll perform

72
00:06:52,779 --> 00:06:53,746
Riding Alone for Thousands of Miles.

73
00:07:01,922 --> 00:07:03,446
I'm not familiar with this particular opera.

74
00:07:05,826 --> 00:07:08,294
It's a mask opera about Lord Guan.

75
00:07:08,628 --> 00:07:10,357
Oh...I see...the Lord Guan...

76
00:07:10,564 --> 00:07:11,428
from the story

77
00:07:11,765 --> 00:07:13,900
The Romance of the Three Kingdoms?

78
00:07:13,900 --> 00:07:15,368
He actually knows

79
00:07:15,368 --> 00:07:17,237
who Lord Guan is.

80
00:07:17,237 --> 00:07:18,305
Riding Alone for Thousands of Miles

81
00:07:18,305 --> 00:07:20,637
is the greatest of all mask operas.

82
00:07:21,541 --> 00:07:24,772
I'm the greatest singer of it.

83
00:07:34,321 --> 00:07:36,289
Then, this is a rare chance.

84
00:07:36,389 --> 00:07:38,323
Can't you sing a little for me now?

85
00:07:39,626 --> 00:07:41,261
My voice is not up to it today.

86
00:07:41,261 --> 00:07:42,888
Ken-ichi is leaving China tonight.

87
00:07:43,964 --> 00:07:45,556
Then, some other time.

88
00:07:50,003 --> 00:07:52,699
It's a deal.

89
00:07:53,073 --> 00:07:54,404
I'll come back to Yunnan next year.

90
00:07:56,810 --> 00:07:59,438
I promise you an unforgettable performance.

91
00:08:10,624 --> 00:08:12,091
How's the catch today?

92
00:08:13,727 --> 00:08:15,558
Nothing much.

93
00:08:26,973 --> 00:08:28,668
This is Takata.

94
00:08:29,743 --> 00:08:31,108
Father

95
00:08:34,781 --> 00:08:37,306
I've been calling and calling.

96
00:08:38,451 --> 00:08:40,749
Have you been fishing?

97
00:08:44,024 --> 00:08:46,959
I've received Ken-ichi's diagnosis.

98
00:08:49,930 --> 00:08:51,761
Cancer of the liver.

99
00:08:53,834 --> 00:08:55,893
It is terminal.

100
00:08:59,840 --> 00:09:02,331
I haven't told Ken-ichi yet.

101
00:09:05,111 --> 00:09:10,674
I don't think...I have the courage.

102
00:09:12,786 --> 00:09:14,617
He thinks

103
00:09:15,689 --> 00:09:18,954
he will be discharged soon.

104
00:09:31,972 --> 00:09:37,638
I've always hoped...in my heart

105
00:09:39,679 --> 00:09:45,845
that our family could enjoy a meal together

106
00:09:48,388 --> 00:09:49,616
Father

107
00:09:50,757 --> 00:09:52,190
Ken-ichi

108
00:09:53,493 --> 00:09:55,017
and l.

109
00:09:59,399 --> 00:10:01,390
Now I'm not sure

110
00:10:02,836 --> 00:10:05,930
that's going to happen.

111
00:10:33,800 --> 00:10:35,233
I need to find

112
00:10:36,002 --> 00:10:39,199
the singer Mr. Li Jiamin.

113
00:10:40,140 --> 00:10:44,804
I don't know what is out there

114
00:10:45,445 --> 00:10:49,211
and I'm not good at dealing with people.

115
00:10:50,016 --> 00:10:51,142
However

116
00:10:52,018 --> 00:10:53,747
I feel compelled to go.

117
00:10:54,020 --> 00:11:00,755
I need to do something for my dying son.

118
00:11:10,971 --> 00:11:12,138
Mr. Takata.

119
00:11:12,138 --> 00:11:14,541
Do you want to rest in Kunming

120
00:11:14,541 --> 00:11:16,609
or go to Lijiang immediately?

121
00:11:16,609 --> 00:11:18,008
Lijiang, immediately.

122
00:11:18,044 --> 00:11:19,773
Fine.

123
00:11:21,614 --> 00:11:25,015
LIJIANG

124
00:11:26,486 --> 00:11:27,748
Rie?

125
00:11:28,188 --> 00:11:29,519
It's me.

126
00:11:32,058 --> 00:11:33,184
I'm at Lijiang

127
00:11:33,593 --> 00:11:37,256
in Yunnan Province, China.

128
00:11:38,131 --> 00:11:39,564
Yunnan?

129
00:11:40,166 --> 00:11:41,599
What are you doing there?

130
00:11:42,569 --> 00:11:45,163
I'm filming "Riding Alone for Thousands of Miles".

131
00:11:46,606 --> 00:11:49,131
You want to film it

132
00:11:49,843 --> 00:11:51,811
for Ken-ichi?

133
00:11:53,947 --> 00:11:55,608
Actually

134
00:11:56,216 --> 00:11:58,844
I gave you that tape

135
00:11:59,285 --> 00:12:03,016
so you could learn more about him.

136
00:12:04,924 --> 00:12:06,323
Father

137
00:12:06,960 --> 00:12:09,758
please come back.

138
00:12:10,130 --> 00:12:11,688
No.

139
00:12:12,799 --> 00:12:15,635
The travel agency has arranged everything.

140
00:12:15,635 --> 00:12:17,262
Please don't be worried about me.

141
00:12:18,004 --> 00:12:19,301
Just don't tell Ken-ichi

142
00:12:21,007 --> 00:12:23,908
what I'm planning.

143
00:12:24,878 --> 00:12:27,142
Please.

144
00:12:40,326 --> 00:12:43,056
LI VILLAGE

145
00:12:44,798 --> 00:12:45,765
Mr. Takata.

146
00:12:45,765 --> 00:12:50,603
This is Lingo. He's a village tour guide.

147
00:12:50,603 --> 00:12:52,798
He speaks a little Japanese.

148
00:13:01,681 --> 00:13:02,248
Lingo.

149
00:13:02,248 --> 00:13:05,151
Remember Ken-ichi was here last year?

150
00:13:05,151 --> 00:13:08,088
He promised to film the mask opera.

151
00:13:08,088 --> 00:13:10,022
This is his father.

152
00:13:11,024 --> 00:13:12,685
So you're Ken-ichi's father.

153
00:13:14,160 --> 00:13:16,924
His father.

154
00:13:17,964 --> 00:13:22,765
Ken-ichi is...my friend.

155
00:13:23,169 --> 00:13:25,069
He's a very...good friend.

156
00:13:44,891 --> 00:13:46,059
Lingo, how is everything going?

157
00:13:46,059 --> 00:13:47,219
Just a second.

158
00:13:48,828 --> 00:13:50,230
Are you Li Jiamin?

159
00:13:50,230 --> 00:13:51,698
No.

160
00:13:51,698 --> 00:13:54,064
Lingo, I told you we only wanted Li.

161
00:13:56,102 --> 00:13:57,303
It doesn't have to be Li.

162
00:13:57,303 --> 00:13:59,639
Other actors can also play Lord Guan.

163
00:13:59,639 --> 00:14:02,267
No way. Mr. Takata only wants Li Jiamin.

164
00:14:02,876 --> 00:14:04,043
If he insists on Li

165
00:14:04,043 --> 00:14:05,912
there will be no show today.

166
00:14:05,912 --> 00:14:07,080
Why not?

167
00:14:07,080 --> 00:14:09,014
Look, Li enjoys a drink or two

168
00:14:09,682 --> 00:14:11,818
which is usually fine.

169
00:14:11,818 --> 00:14:12,352
Then, during a rehearsal

170
00:14:12,352 --> 00:14:15,121
a stage hand mentioned

171
00:14:15,121 --> 00:14:17,248
he had a bastard son.

172
00:14:17,290 --> 00:14:19,792
This upset him so much

173
00:14:19,792 --> 00:14:22,226
that he grabbed a wooden dagger

174
00:14:22,695 --> 00:14:25,298
and stabbed the guy in the face.

175
00:14:25,298 --> 00:14:28,392
He was arrested

176
00:14:28,801 --> 00:14:30,325
and sentenced to 3 years in prison.

177
00:14:31,804 --> 00:14:32,438
Please tell him

178
00:14:32,438 --> 00:14:35,669
it doesn't have to be Li Jiamin performing.

179
00:14:37,010 --> 00:14:39,001
All the actors are very good.

180
00:14:39,479 --> 00:14:42,107
Once the mask is on

181
00:14:44,150 --> 00:14:46,419
it doesn't matter who is behind it.

182
00:14:46,419 --> 00:14:48,080
No-one can tell the difference.

183
00:14:48,888 --> 00:14:50,219
Even a native can't tell

184
00:14:50,823 --> 00:14:53,493
the difference between the voices.

185
00:14:53,493 --> 00:14:55,358
So how could a Japanese person?

186
00:15:03,102 --> 00:15:04,904
Does it really have to be Li?

187
00:15:04,904 --> 00:15:07,040
His son wanted to film Li.

188
00:15:07,040 --> 00:15:09,108
He is making this film for his son.

189
00:15:09,108 --> 00:15:10,803
No-one else will do.

190
00:15:11,144 --> 00:15:13,442
But Li Jiamin is in prison

191
00:15:13,846 --> 00:15:15,040
for 3 years.

192
00:15:16,216 --> 00:15:17,450
Even if he behaves well

193
00:15:17,450 --> 00:15:19,152
and becomes a model prisoner

194
00:15:19,152 --> 00:15:21,416
he won't be released for a year or two.

195
00:15:22,088 --> 00:15:23,790
Takata should come back.

196
00:15:23,790 --> 00:15:25,158
There will be other chances.

197
00:15:25,158 --> 00:15:26,785
The show is always playing.

198
00:15:41,908 --> 00:15:43,068
Jasmine

199
00:15:43,977 --> 00:15:45,740
please help me.

200
00:15:46,346 --> 00:15:50,049
Mr. Takata, this is not about money.

201
00:15:50,049 --> 00:15:52,449
I'm in a difficult position.

202
00:15:52,885 --> 00:15:55,021
I'm just a tour guide.

203
00:15:55,021 --> 00:15:57,319
How can I get a foreigner

204
00:15:57,523 --> 00:16:02,929
permission to film inside a prison?

205
00:16:02,929 --> 00:16:04,829
It is impossible.

206
00:16:05,565 --> 00:16:09,802
Please help me.

207
00:16:09,802 --> 00:16:12,939
I really want to help.

208
00:16:12,939 --> 00:16:15,975
But this is beyond my ability

209
00:16:15,975 --> 00:16:18,211
and my job description.

210
00:16:18,211 --> 00:16:20,179
Please forgive me.

211
00:16:22,148 --> 00:16:24,343
My contract is only for 3 days.

212
00:16:24,517 --> 00:16:28,078
I've been assigned other jobs.

213
00:16:28,288 --> 00:16:36,388
I'll see you off at Kunming Airport.

214
00:16:37,063 --> 00:16:38,223
I'm sorry.

215
00:16:43,036 --> 00:16:44,203
Jasmine

216
00:16:44,203 --> 00:16:47,940
please ask your boss

217
00:16:47,940 --> 00:16:51,467
if I could employ another interpreter.

218
00:17:11,864 --> 00:17:13,889
Hi, Boss. This is Jasmine.

219
00:17:15,335 --> 00:17:17,036
That Japanese tourist

220
00:17:17,036 --> 00:17:19,436
Mr. Takata, who arrived 2 days ago

221
00:17:20,039 --> 00:17:22,303
is asking for a new interpreter.

222
00:17:34,921 --> 00:17:36,081
Mr. Takata

223
00:17:37,323 --> 00:17:40,053
my boss cannot help with your plan

224
00:17:40,193 --> 00:17:41,990
to film inside the prison.

225
00:17:42,328 --> 00:17:44,387
He also says

226
00:17:44,564 --> 00:17:47,667
he doesn't have another interpreter available.

227
00:17:47,667 --> 00:17:50,864
Please forget about this idea.

228
00:17:56,042 --> 00:17:57,043
Mr. Takata.

229
00:17:57,043 --> 00:17:58,111
Is that actor, Mr. Li, so important

230
00:17:58,111 --> 00:18:00,909
to your film?

231
00:18:11,958 --> 00:18:13,084
Excuse me.

232
00:18:14,127 --> 00:18:15,219
Please turn around.

233
00:18:16,129 --> 00:18:17,562
Turn around.

234
00:18:18,264 --> 00:18:19,595
Turn around.

235
00:18:21,501 --> 00:18:22,435
Jasmine

236
00:18:22,435 --> 00:18:24,300
he wants to go back.

237
00:18:31,144 --> 00:18:32,011
The opera is

238
00:18:32,011 --> 00:18:34,946
Riding Alone for Thousands of Miles.

239
00:18:36,349 --> 00:18:38,184
Lord Guan traveled a thousand miles

240
00:18:38,184 --> 00:18:41,244
to help a friend

241
00:18:42,255 --> 00:18:44,190
which is a big deal.

242
00:18:44,190 --> 00:18:46,351
A man must be loyal.

243
00:18:47,994 --> 00:18:52,431
I can't understand what they are saying

244
00:18:52,999 --> 00:18:56,560
but I need their help.

245
00:18:57,036 --> 00:19:01,996
Without them, I can't go anywhere.

246
00:19:03,142 --> 00:19:07,943
For the first time, I feel helpless.

247
00:19:09,115 --> 00:19:15,418
I wonder if Ken-ichi would feel the same way.

248
00:19:19,692 --> 00:19:21,023
Mr. Takata

249
00:19:26,599 --> 00:19:27,531
about your plan

250
00:19:28,234 --> 00:19:29,462
Jasmine cannot help you

251
00:19:29,769 --> 00:19:32,636
but I am able to.

252
00:19:34,373 --> 00:19:35,635
Much obliged.

253
00:19:36,242 --> 00:19:37,470
Thank you.

254
00:19:37,543 --> 00:19:40,171
No problem.

255
00:19:45,651 --> 00:19:47,787
There are no costumes

256
00:19:47,787 --> 00:19:52,225
or props in the prison.

257
00:19:52,225 --> 00:19:53,693
We'll have to take them.

258
00:19:53,693 --> 00:19:56,389
Excuse me.

259
00:19:57,997 --> 00:20:00,366
There are no props and costumes at the prison.

260
00:20:00,366 --> 00:20:03,733
He's getting them.

261
00:20:06,639 --> 00:20:07,607
Mr. Takata

262
00:20:07,607 --> 00:20:09,775
I must confide in you.

263
00:20:09,775 --> 00:20:12,445
Lingo is my friend.

264
00:20:12,445 --> 00:20:14,013
He is very enthusiastic

265
00:20:14,013 --> 00:20:17,283
but he really doesn't know much.

266
00:20:17,283 --> 00:20:18,351
So, let me tell you

267
00:20:18,351 --> 00:20:20,410
the basic procedures to follow.

268
00:20:39,405 --> 00:20:41,805
First, go to the Office of Foreign Affairs.

269
00:20:42,341 --> 00:20:45,276
Tell them why you want to visit the prison.

270
00:20:45,778 --> 00:20:48,440
Office of Foreign Affairs.

271
00:20:49,181 --> 00:20:51,083
If they approve

272
00:20:51,083 --> 00:20:52,812
then go to the Bureau of Justice.

273
00:20:53,619 --> 00:20:55,849
Bureau of Justice.

274
00:20:56,255 --> 00:20:58,090
If they approve

275
00:20:58,090 --> 00:21:00,115
then all's well.

276
00:21:00,593 --> 00:21:05,155
Bureau of Justice...approves

277
00:21:05,798 --> 00:21:07,233
If you have any difficulties

278
00:21:07,233 --> 00:21:10,803
or Lingo can't properly translate for you

279
00:21:10,803 --> 00:21:12,471
please call me.

280
00:21:12,471 --> 00:21:15,099
I'll translate for you over the phone.

281
00:21:15,641 --> 00:21:19,634
You have my phone number.

282
00:21:21,747 --> 00:21:24,511
I'll leave this car for you

283
00:21:24,750 --> 00:21:26,581
and charge it to your account.

284
00:21:28,287 --> 00:21:29,413
You need to sign this form.

285
00:21:31,557 --> 00:21:37,655
It's your request to change the interpreter.

286
00:21:38,898 --> 00:21:39,762
Please sign here.

