He couldn't sing.

583
00:42:21,773 --> 00:42:23,641
Li wasn't like that before.

584
00:42:23,641 --> 00:42:26,804
He is a different man in prison.

585
00:42:27,645 --> 00:42:30,648
Please pass the phone to Takata.

586
00:42:30,648 --> 00:42:32,115
I'll explain to him.

587
00:42:34,419 --> 00:42:36,614
Mr. Takata, your phone.

588
00:42:37,555 --> 00:42:39,523
It's me.

589
00:42:57,876 --> 00:42:59,104
Jasmine.

590
00:43:00,879 --> 00:43:01,868
This is Takata.

591
00:43:02,380 --> 00:43:03,381
Mr. Takata.

592
00:43:03,381 --> 00:43:04,609
Sorry to disturb you so late.

593
00:43:05,817 --> 00:43:12,620
I've been thinking.

594
00:43:14,092 --> 00:43:18,426
I've decided to bring Li's son to him.

595
00:43:19,397 --> 00:43:21,831
You want to bring the boy to Li?

596
00:43:22,834 --> 00:43:23,698
Yes.

597
00:43:24,202 --> 00:43:26,170
Please reconsider, Mr. Takata.

598
00:43:26,170 --> 00:43:30,642
Li was over emotional today.

599
00:43:30,642 --> 00:43:32,510
Warden Chen said

600
00:43:32,510 --> 00:43:34,705
he'd be fine in a few days.

601
00:43:35,413 --> 00:43:38,549
The boy lives in Stone Village.

602
00:43:38,549 --> 00:43:42,754
It is in a very remote place.

603
00:43:42,754 --> 00:43:44,483
This detour will only delay your plan.

604
00:43:45,223 --> 00:43:48,750
I've made up my mind.

605
00:43:49,994 --> 00:43:50,862
Mr. Takata.

606
00:43:50,862 --> 00:43:52,697
Isn't making the film for Ken-ichi

607
00:43:52,697 --> 00:43:56,030
the most important thing?

608
00:43:57,835 --> 00:44:02,932
Both are of equal importance now.

609
00:44:04,976 --> 00:44:08,846
I'm sorry.

610
00:44:08,846 --> 00:44:10,905
Please call Lingo now

611
00:44:11,482 --> 00:44:12,710
and ask him to take me to Stone Village tomorrow.

612
00:44:13,117 --> 00:44:14,948
Please, I'm sorry.

613
00:44:15,186 --> 00:44:16,153
All right.

614
00:44:35,773 --> 00:44:37,475
Lingo.

615
00:44:37,475 --> 00:44:38,737
Good evening. May l?

616
00:44:38,776 --> 00:44:39,572
Please.

617
00:44:45,083 --> 00:44:45,850
What is it?

618
00:44:45,850 --> 00:44:46,908
Good night.

619
00:44:49,053 --> 00:44:50,020
Goodbye.

620
00:45:03,534 --> 00:45:04,168
Hello.

621
00:45:04,168 --> 00:45:06,304
Is this Mr. Takata?

622
00:45:06,304 --> 00:45:08,272
Sorry to bother you again.

623
00:45:09,307 --> 00:45:15,576
What did you say to Lingo?

624
00:45:15,813 --> 00:45:17,542
Why did he

625
00:45:18,049 --> 00:45:24,079
return the money to me?

626
00:45:25,256 --> 00:45:29,317
Will he still help me tomorrow?

627
00:45:30,061 --> 00:45:31,529
Mr. Takata.

628
00:45:31,529 --> 00:45:33,156
Let me explain.

629
00:45:34,532 --> 00:45:36,693
Lingo and I feel very sad

630
00:45:38,669 --> 00:45:40,000
about Ken-ichi's illness.

631
00:45:40,571 --> 00:45:42,903
I apologize

632
00:45:43,908 --> 00:45:45,743
for not helping you earlier.

633
00:45:45,743 --> 00:45:46,869
Forgive me.

634
00:45:47,211 --> 00:45:48,576
Never mind.

635
00:45:50,148 --> 00:45:52,582
I understand.

636
00:45:53,217 --> 00:45:56,220
Lingo doesn't feel right

637
00:45:56,220 --> 00:45:58,089
about taking your money

638
00:45:58,089 --> 00:46:01,684
when your son is so sick.

639
00:46:03,094 --> 00:46:03,961
He will still take you

640
00:46:03,961 --> 00:46:07,692
to Stone Village tomorrow.

641
00:46:10,835 --> 00:46:11,893
Really?

642
00:46:13,171 --> 00:46:14,604
Thank you both.

643
00:46:17,875 --> 00:46:21,174
I'm happy that Ken-ichi

644
00:46:22,580 --> 00:46:23,205
has friends like you.

645
00:46:26,751 --> 00:46:30,084
Does he have many friends in China?

646
00:46:30,888 --> 00:46:34,221
Actually...I don't know Ken-ichi.

647
00:46:34,959 --> 00:46:38,690
Lingo doesn't know him very well either.

648
00:46:39,697 --> 00:46:41,332
Lingo said that

649
00:46:41,332 --> 00:46:45,769
Ken-ichi hardly has any friends in China.

650
00:46:47,138 --> 00:46:48,400
Really?

651
00:46:49,240 --> 00:46:51,105
Lingo said

652
00:46:51,409 --> 00:46:54,401
Ken-ichi seldom spoke to anyone.

653
00:46:54,912 --> 00:46:59,906
He would stay alone in Lijiang for months.

654
00:47:00,852 --> 00:47:03,321
Sometimes he just stared for hours

655
00:47:03,321 --> 00:47:05,152
at the mountains.

656
00:47:06,124 --> 00:47:09,685
He seemed very lonely.

657
00:47:14,132 --> 00:47:17,268
I may have said too much.

658
00:47:17,268 --> 00:47:18,326
No.

659
00:47:20,905 --> 00:47:22,099
Please

660
00:47:23,441 --> 00:47:27,172
tell me more about my son.

661
00:47:28,846 --> 00:47:32,984
Mr. Takata, I'm afraid that's all I know.

662
00:47:32,984 --> 00:47:34,110
I am sorry.

663
00:47:35,319 --> 00:47:36,411
Never mind.

664
00:47:37,455 --> 00:47:40,253
I'm sorry it's so late.

665
00:47:40,658 --> 00:47:43,261
Thank you, Jasmine.

666
00:47:43,261 --> 00:47:44,956
Good night.

667
00:48:45,056 --> 00:48:46,523
There's road work ahead.

668
00:49:07,511 --> 00:49:12,414
STONE Village

669
00:49:18,489 --> 00:49:20,889
Yang Yang's mom died a week ago.

670
00:49:21,259 --> 00:49:24,862
He has no other family to care for him.

671
00:49:24,862 --> 00:49:28,132
The villagers are taking care of him now.

672
00:49:28,132 --> 00:49:30,034
The village chief said

673
00:49:30,034 --> 00:49:33,170
the boy is now being raised by everyone

674
00:49:33,170 --> 00:49:34,572
in this village.

675
00:49:34,572 --> 00:49:36,140
That's right.

676
00:49:36,140 --> 00:49:38,335
Li was told about this.

677
00:49:39,143 --> 00:49:41,879
That's why he broke down in prison.

678
00:49:41,879 --> 00:49:43,047
This was the reason.

679
00:49:43,047 --> 00:49:46,384
We know why you have come here.

680
00:49:46,384 --> 00:49:48,875
Our committee has already made its decision

681
00:49:50,921 --> 00:49:54,049
I cannot give you the details straight away.

682
00:49:54,525 --> 00:49:55,492
Why not?

683
00:49:56,494 --> 00:49:58,262
Before I explain

684
00:49:58,262 --> 00:50:00,822
I must clarify some things.

685
00:50:02,300 --> 00:50:03,528
Please translate what I say.

686
00:50:04,135 --> 00:50:05,136
Of course I will.

687
00:50:05,136 --> 00:50:06,504
He's my client.

688
00:50:06,504 --> 00:50:07,869
Please continue.

689
00:50:08,306 --> 00:50:11,309
I want to say two things.

690
00:50:11,309 --> 00:50:13,038
Firstly

691
00:50:13,511 --> 00:50:16,002
Yang Yang is Li's son

692
00:50:17,581 --> 00:50:20,072
born outside of wedlock

693
00:50:20,851 --> 00:50:23,149
but we all accept that.

694
00:50:23,521 --> 00:50:24,453
We all agree.

695
00:50:25,189 --> 00:50:26,121
This is the first point.

696
00:50:26,424 --> 00:50:27,224
Secondly

697
00:50:27,224 --> 00:50:30,828
After 8 years, Li has now decided to claim his son.

698
00:50:30,828 --> 00:50:32,557
We don't have a problem with this.

699
00:50:34,098 --> 00:50:35,463
You'd better translate now.

700
00:50:36,334 --> 00:50:39,064
Why don't you simply say "yes" or "no"?

701
00:50:39,236 --> 00:50:41,172
So I can give him an answer now.

702
00:50:41,172 --> 00:50:42,537
Yes or "no"?

703
00:50:43,407 --> 00:50:46,210
You haven't translated a single word to him.

704
00:50:46,210 --> 00:50:48,145
You should translate everything I've said.

705
00:50:48,145 --> 00:50:49,544
You should make yourself clear before I do.

706
00:50:52,283 --> 00:50:54,485
I doubt you speak any Japanese.

707
00:50:54,485 --> 00:50:56,578
Ridiculous. Of course I do.

708
00:51:02,059 --> 00:51:05,426
This loud discussion is going on for a long time.

709
00:51:06,430 --> 00:51:10,196
I suddenly feel like an outsider.

710
00:51:12,136 --> 00:51:13,170
I realize

711
00:51:13,170 --> 00:51:14,330
in a foreign language environment

712
00:51:16,540 --> 00:51:19,475
you can feel very isolated.

713
00:51:20,878 --> 00:51:21,640
I'm slowly

714
00:51:22,446 --> 00:51:26,246
beginning to understand

715
00:51:27,218 --> 00:51:29,618
why Ken-ichi often visits here.

716
00:51:31,489 --> 00:51:35,126
You're supposed to be a translator.

717
00:51:35,126 --> 00:51:38,027
I wouldn't need you if I spoke Japanese.

718
00:51:39,263 --> 00:51:40,164
I know how to translate.

719
00:51:40,164 --> 00:51:42,132
I beg to differ on that.

720
00:51:45,035 --> 00:51:46,127
No signal.

721
00:51:46,537 --> 00:51:49,473
There's no signal here.

722
00:51:49,473 --> 00:51:51,964
I know where you can get one.

723
00:51:52,977 --> 00:51:54,945
He's calling a translator.

724
00:51:55,379 --> 00:51:57,040
Let's go outside.

725
00:52:18,068 --> 00:52:20,304
Why are we going to the roof?

726
00:52:20,304 --> 00:52:21,605
You can get a stronger signal.

727
00:52:21,605 --> 00:52:23,470
My son has made calls from up here before.

728
00:52:40,524 --> 00:52:42,082
Who is Mr. Takata calling?

729
00:52:43,160 --> 00:52:45,963
Jasmine, a translator from Kunming.

730
00:52:45,963 --> 00:52:48,199
Isn't that your job?

731
00:52:48,199 --> 00:52:49,633
Are you sure you speak Japanese?

732
00:52:49,633 --> 00:52:50,701
Of course I do.

733
00:52:50,701 --> 00:52:52,303
The issue is so important

734
00:52:52,303 --> 00:52:53,571
we need to get a true professional.

735
00:52:53,571 --> 00:52:54,970
Jasmine.

736
00:52:56,574 --> 00:52:57,734
I'm sorry.

737
00:52:58,275 --> 00:53:01,108
I don't understand what is being said.

738
00:53:01,412 --> 00:53:02,713
Can you translate for me?

739
00:53:02,713 --> 00:53:04,146
Thank you.

740
00:53:10,287 --> 00:53:11,447
Ms Translator.

741
00:53:11,755 --> 00:53:14,246
I want to make two points.

742
00:53:14,525 --> 00:53:18,462
Firstly, Li didn't register a legal marriage

743
00:53:18,462 --> 00:53:20,264
before his son was born.

744
00:53:20,264 --> 00:53:22,166
We all accept that

745
00:53:22,166 --> 00:53:23,360
Yang Yang is Li's son.

746
00:53:24,268 --> 00:53:25,402
This is point one.

747
00:53:25,402 --> 00:53:26,337
Secondly

748
00:53:26,337 --> 00:53:29,306
at 8 years of age the boy

749
00:53:29,306 --> 00:53:31,475
now finds he's got a father.

750
00:53:31,475 --> 00:53:34,011
Li's sudden interest is hard to believe

751
00:53:34,011 --> 00:53:36,113
and is confusing for everyone.

752
00:53:36,113 --> 00:53:38,081
Please translate this for him.

753
00:53:40,618 --> 00:53:41,676
It's me.

754
00:53:46,156 --> 00:53:47,623
I totally understand

755
00:53:48,425 --> 00:53:49,790
their reservations.

756
00:53:55,399 --> 00:53:57,663
I never said "no" on this matter.

757
00:53:58,502 --> 00:54:00,697
Lingo can't speak a word of Japanese.

758
00:54:01,539 --> 00:54:03,240
Mr. Takata needed to know

759
00:54:03,240 --> 00:54:05,509
our feelings on the subject.

760
00:54:05,509 --> 00:54:07,033
Now he really understands

761
00:54:07,411 --> 00:54:09,311
we are very relieved.

762
00:54:10,114 --> 00:54:12,082
We have no more issues.

763
00:54:12,516 --> 00:54:16,213
After much discussion, we give our consent

764
00:54:16,754 --> 00:54:19,590
to let the boy go. Not for Li's sake

765
00:54:19,590 --> 00:54:22,626
but for the sake of our Japanese friend.

766
00:54:22,626 --> 00:54:24,595
Yang Yang can visit his father

767
00:54:24,595 --> 00:54:26,460
with Mr. Takata tomorrow.

768
00:54:55,159 --> 00:54:56,421
Yang Yang.

769
00:54:56,794 --> 00:54:58,386
This is Yang Yang.

770
00:55:18,882 --> 00:55:20,884
You are going to town tomorrow.

771
00:55:20,884 --> 00:55:22,545
Get him some new clothes.

772
00:55:26,690 --> 00:55:30,421
Could you ask the Chief

773
00:55:31,328 --> 00:55:35,128
if Yang Yang wants to see his father?

774
00:55:36,700 --> 00:55:37,601
Chief

775
00:55:37,601 --> 00:55:38,936
he asks

776
00:55:38,936 --> 00:55:40,733
if Yang Yang wants to see his father.

777
00:55:41,639 --> 00:55:42,940
No problem.

778
00:55:42,940 --> 00:55:46,205
Of course he does.

779
00:55:46,877 --> 00:55:50,870
No problem.

780
00:55:51,582 --> 00:55:51,809
Sure?

781
00:55:53,217 --> 00:55:53,683
Yes.

782
00:56:02,660 --> 00:56:03,820
One moment.

783
00:56:04,361 --> 00:56:05,419
I have to take a call.

784
00:56:19,176 --> 00:56:20,234
This is Rie.

785
00:56:20,978 --> 00:56:24,573
Father, please don't be upset.

786
00:56:26,617 --> 00:56:28,676
I've told Ken-ichi

787
00:56:30,454 --> 00:56:32,581
about your trip to China.

788
00:56:36,827 --> 00:56:41,491
He didn't say a word the whole night

789
00:56:42,299 --> 00:56:44,494
after he heard this

790
00:56:46,837 --> 00:56:51,706
but he looked different.

791
00:56:53,844 --> 00:56:56,506
I could see a change in his eyes.

792
00:56:59,583 --> 00:57:00,743
Father

793
00:57:01,685 --> 00:57:04,586
he never expected that

794
00:57:05,389 --> 00:57:07,619
you would do such a thing for him.

795
00:57:07,925 --> 00:57:11,452
Ken-ichi told me today

796
00:57:11,929 --> 00:57:15,490
this particular piece of mask opera

797
00:57:16,433 --> 00:57:18,264
is not that important to him.

798
00:57:18,969 --> 00:57:21,699
He was only being polite to Li.

799
00:57:26,243 --> 00:57:30,270
So, Father, please come back.

800
00:57:35,419 --> 00:57:36,579
Father

801
00:57:37,554 --> 00:57:38,612
can you hear me?

802
00:57:41,325 --> 00:57:42,724
I am listening.

803
00:57:44,695 --> 00:57:45,684
Father

804
00:57:47,397 --> 00:57:48,694
please come home.

805
00:57:56,039 --> 00:57:57,472
Ken-ichi said

806
00:57:58,876 --> 00:58:01,071
your trip to China

807
00:58:02,379 --> 00:58:03,676
is the most wonderful thing

808
00:58:04,314 --> 00:58:07,283
you've done for him.

809
00:58:11,588 --> 00:58:15,046
Did Ken-ichi say that?

810
00:58:15,726 --> 00:58:16,818
Yes

811
00:58:18,796 --> 00:58:22,527
these are his exact words.

812
00:58:28,639 --> 00:58:30,300
Thank you.

813
00:58:34,077 --> 00:58:35,339
Standing here today

814
00:58:35,712 --> 00:58:37,373
I'm not sure

815
00:58:38,916 --> 00:58:40,611
if Ken-ichi has uttered these words.

816
00:58:41,685 --> 00:58:44,449
If he has

817
00:58:46,323 --> 00:58:48,450
it is the first compliment

818
00:58:49,426 --> 00:58:54,864
from my son in many years.

819
00:58:56,700 --> 00:58:58,065
Seeing this large banquet

820
00:58:59,002 --> 00:59:01,596
prepared by the villagers

821
00:59:02,773 --> 00:59:04,138
for me a total stranger

822
00:59:05,642 --> 00:59:08,941
I am deeply touched.

823
00:59:10,480 --> 00:59:11,777
I will never forget this.

824
00:59:13,083 --> 00:59:15,381
The sight of such generosity

825
00:59:16,653 --> 00:59:18,484
and kindness from the villagers

826
00:59:19,890 --> 00:59:20,914
makes me want to believe

827
00:59:21,491 --> 00:59:23,118
that Ken-ichi has said these words.

828
01:00:17,781 --> 01:00:18,916
What's wrong?

829
01:00:18,916 --> 01:00:19,712
The tractor's broken down.

830
01:00:20,951 --> 01:00:21,747
Broken down.

831
01:00:21,919 --> 01:00:22,749
Really?

832
01:00:22,986 --> 01:00:23,782
Yes

833
01:00:25,122 --> 01:00:26,111
Can you fix it?

834
01:00:27,224 --> 01:00:29,658
I think so. Let me try.

835
01:01:45,535 --> 01:01:46,695
Yang Yang!

836
01:01:54,611 --> 01:01:55,703
Yang Yang!

837
01:01:58,582 --> 01:01:59,674
Lingo!

838
01:02:44,027 --> 01:02:45,551
Lingo!

839
01:03:03,380 --> 01:03:05,371
Yang Yang! Mr. Takata!

840
01:03:05,949 --> 01:03:06,973
Yang Yang!

841
01:03:09,719 --> 01:03:11,016
Mr. Takata!

842
01:03:14,091 --> 01:03:15,115
Mr. Takata!

843
01:03:30,307 --> 01:03:31,365
Yang Yang.

844
01:03:40,984 --> 01:03:42,178
What's the matter?

845
01:03:43,620 --> 01:03:44,780
Why did you run away from us?

846
01:03:58,201 --> 01:04:01,637
Do you know your way home?

847
01:04:02,772 --> 01:04:03,932
Going home?

848
01:04:05,342 --> 01:04:06,707
Your home.

849
01:04:14,151 --> 01:04:15,675
Why are you running away?

850
01:04:24,294 --> 01:04:25,226
Yang Yang.

851
01:04:27,764 --> 01:04:28,856
Do you know where you're going?

852
01:04:33,803 --> 01:04:34,462
Yang Yang

853
01:04:36,806 --> 01:04:37,795
are you going home?

854
01:04:45,315 --> 01:04:46,373
Is this the right direction?

855
01:04:54,291 --> 01:04:58,728
Hurry up everyone!

856
01:05:18,348 --> 01:05:19,781
It seems like hours.

857
01:05:20,217 --> 01:05:25,416
All I can do is to follow Yang Yang around.

858
01:05:26,456 --> 01:05:27,388
I'm one step behind. I think

859
01:05:27,824 --> 01:05:31,828
the way I'm chasing after him

860
01:05:31,828 --> 01:05:37,960
is the way I chase after my own son.

861
01:05:41,972 --> 01:05:43,030
I don't know

862
01:05:44,808 --> 01:05:46,833
which path to take

863
01:05:47,510 --> 01:05:49,171
or what direction to go.

864
01:05:50,347 --> 01:05:51,939
I have no idea.

865
01:05:57,854 --> 01:05:59,014
Yang Yang.

866
01:06:02,425 --> 01:06:04,359
We've been here before.

867
01:06:07,063 --> 01:06:08,826
The trail looks the same.

868
01:06:10,400 --> 01:06:11,765
Do you see?

869
01:06:15,238 --> 01:06:16,227
Yang Yang.

870
01:06:21,511 --> 01:06:22,569
We are lost.

871
01:06:28,585 --> 01:06:30,018
We are very lost.

872
01:06:35,191 --> 01:06:37,022
We can't keep going like this.

873
01:06:40,230 --> 01:06:42,494
Let's wait for someone to find us.

874
01:06:50,607 --> 01:06:51,574
All right.

875
01:06:53,376 --> 01:06:56,504
Let's find a place to rest.

876
01:07:15,498 --> 01:07:16,590
Let's wait here

877
01:07:18,001 --> 01:07:20,970
and stay out of the wind.

878
01:07:39,589 --> 01:07:43,582
Yang Yang.

879
01:08:00,143 --> 01:08:01,508
What are you doing?

880
01:08:07,083 --> 01:08:08,345
Having a poo-poo?

881
01:08:09,252 --> 01:08:10,514
I thought you were running off again.

882
01:08:12,622 --> 01:08:13,490
Don't look.

883
01:08:13,490 --> 01:08:15,925
I can't do it if you watch.

884
01:08:15,925 --> 01:08:17,085
Go away.

885
01:08:22,198 --> 01:08:24,462
I don't believe this.

886
01:08:27,270 --> 01:08:28,669
Go away.

887
01:08:29,706 --> 01:08:30,907
Go away.

888
01:08:30,907 --> 01:08:32,976
I'm not leaving.

889
01:08:32,976 --> 01:08:34,273
I'll stay here.

890
01:08:49,926 --> 01:08:51,393
Go away.

891
01:09:08,178 --> 01:09:10,112
Stop doing that!

892
01:09:11,014 --> 01:09:13,380
Stop doing that!

893
01:09:21,758 --> 01:09:23,623
Go away.

894
01:09:31,000 --> 01:09:33,369
Yang Yang.

895
01:09:33,369 --> 01:09:35,305
Yang Yang.

896
01:09:35,305 --> 01:09:37,205
Hold on

897
01:09:37,607 --> 01:09:40,276
Let's split into two groups to search.

898
01:09:40,276 --> 01:09:42,107
That would be more efficient.

899
01:09:42,679 --> 01:09:44,647
All right, let's do it.

900
01:09:44,647 --> 01:09:46,716
Lingo, how do you pronounce his name?

901
01:09:46,716 --> 01:09:47,784
Mr. Takata.

902
01:09:47,784 --> 01:09:49,012
Are you sure?

903
01:09:50,086 --> 01:09:51,354
Of course. It's a simple name.

904
01:09:51,354 --> 01:09:53,219
Can you teach everyone to say it?

905
01:09:54,624 --> 01:09:56,493
It's pronounced as Mr. Takata.

906
01:09:56,493 --> 01:09:57,760
Repeat with me.

907
01:09:57,760 --> 01:09:59,091
Mr. Takata.

908
01:09:59,562 --> 01:10:00,586
Mr. Takata.

909
01:10:01,331 --> 01:10:02,491
Say it louder. Mr. Takata.

910
01:10:02,532 --> 01:10:03,700
Mr. Takata!

911
01:10:03,700 --> 01:10:05,497
All right.

912
01:10:06,169 --> 01:10:08,538
You lead them that way.

913
01:10:08,538 --> 01:10:09,630
We'll go this way.

914
01:10:10,139 --> 01:10:11,674
Keep yelling out their names.

915
01:10:11,674 --> 01:10:13,665
Let's go.

916
01:10:14,444 --> 01:10:15,376
Mr. Takata!

917
01:10:15,512 --> 01:10:16,501
Yang Yang!

918
01:10:28,591 --> 01:10:32,493
The moon is bright in the sky.

919
01:10:36,132 --> 01:10:38,123
Don't be afraid, Yang Yang.

920
01:10:39,736 --> 01:10:42,296
I'm sure they'll find us.

921
01:10:45,241 --> 01:10:48,233
We have to get their attention.

922
01:10:50,480 --> 01:10:53,278
They might not see us in here.

923
01:11:06,829 --> 01:11:09,127
Lingo!

924
01:11:32,155 --> 01:11:34,749
Here, I've got a boat whistle.

925
01:12:19,802 --> 01:12:20,894
Well done.

926
01:12:21,537 --> 01:12:23,139
Well done, Yang Yang.

927
01:12:23,139 --> 01:12:25,369
No, you keep it.

928
01:12:26,175 --> 01:12:28,268
Blow it again.

929
01:12:34,784 --> 01:12:35,910
Well done.

930
01:12:43,559 --> 01:12:44,753
Well done.

931
01:14:15,651 --> 01:14:17,312
Sitting here all night

932
01:14:18,855 --> 01:14:20,948
waiting to be found

933
01:14:21,824 --> 01:14:22,882
I'm holding Yang Yang tightly in my arms.

934
01:14:23,559 --> 01:14:25,527
I don't remember

935
01:14:26,496 --> 01:14:34,665
if Ken-ichi and l

936
01:14:37,673 --> 01:14:38,697
have ever held

937
01:14:39,442 --> 01:14:43,879
each other like this.

938
01:14:49,285 --> 01:14:51,048
Yang Yang

939
01:14:52,021 --> 01:14:56,958
has no idea what his father even looks like.

940
01:14:58,928 --> 01:15:00,759
I wonder

941
01:15:01,030 --> 01:15:05,967
what kind of father I am to Ken-ichi?

942
01:15:24,420 --> 01:15:26,354
His blood pressure is normal.

943
01:15:26,989 --> 01:15:28,354
You will be fine.

944
01:15:29,792 --> 01:15:31,327
Thank you.

945
01:15:31,327 --> 01:15:32,521
Not at all.

946
01:15:33,462 --> 01:15:36,090
I need to check the boy.

947
01:15:38,668 --> 01:15:39,760
Give me your hand.

948
01:15:49,979 --> 01:15:50,968
Jasmine

949
01:15:52,682 --> 01:15:54,547
could I talk to the Chief please?

950
01:16:05,094 --> 01:16:06,561
I am sorry for causing all this trouble.

951
01:16:08,497 --> 01:16:09,589
No problem.

952
01:16:11,067 --> 01:16:12,625
May I ask

953
01:16:13,502 --> 01:16:17,598
why Yang Yang ran away yesterday?

954
01:16:21,444 --> 01:16:23,742
He often wanders away.

955
01:16:29,952 --> 01:16:31,442
I am not so sure.

956
01:16:32,521 --> 01:16:34,045
Shall we ask Yang Yang?

957
01:16:35,091 --> 01:16:40,825
Maybe he doesn't want to see his father after all.

958
01:16:46,435 --> 01:16:47,803
There is no need to ask.

959
01:16:47,803 --> 01:16:49,005
We'll make the decision for him.

960
01:16:49,005 --> 01:16:50,907
What the hell does a child know?

961
01:16:50,907 --> 01:16:52,966
He has to do as we say.

962
01:16:53,643 --> 01:16:55,975
She can't translate if you're all speaking at once

963
01:16:56,412 --> 01:16:58,614
Shut up. You can't speak Japanese anyway.

964
01:16:58,614 --> 01:16:59,672
I can't? Can you?

965
01:16:59,715 --> 01:17:01,410
You know I can't. Neither can you!

966
01:17:01,450 --> 01:17:04,078
They're arguing again.

967
01:17:13,462 --> 01:17:16,556
We should ask Yang Yang what he wants.

968
01:17:21,037 --> 01:17:22,834
Okay, let me ask him.

969
01:17:27,209 --> 01:17:28,699
Yang Yang, come.

970
01:17:31,747 --> 01:17:33,237
Sit over here.

971
01:17:34,984 --> 01:17:36,110
Let me ask you something.

972
01:17:38,220 --> 01:17:40,950
Do you want to meet your dad?

973
01:17:43,693 --> 01:17:45,661
Do you?

974
01:17:45,661 --> 01:17:48,459
Come on. Yes or no?

975
01:17:49,899 --> 01:17:50,923
No.

976
01:17:51,100 --> 01:17:52,268
Why not?

977
01:17:52,268 --> 01:17:53,963
Don't be naughty.

978
01:17:55,104 --> 01:17:56,503
I am not going!

979
01:17:56,839 --> 01:17:57,806
Why?

980
01:18:00,676 --> 01:18:01,904
Tell me why not?

981
01:18:03,012 --> 01:18:06,682
You must do as the adults say.

982
01:18:06,682 --> 01:18:09,549
I'm telling you to go.

983
01:18:10,553 --> 01:18:11,487
Go now.

984
01:18:11,487 --> 01:18:12,715
He's not my dad.

985
01:18:13,155 --> 01:18:15,491
I've never seen him before.

986
01:18:15,491 --> 01:18:18,016
He is your dad no matter what.

987
01:18:20,262 --> 01:18:21,752
I'm not going.

988
01:18:23,532 --> 01:18:25,693
Why don't you want to see your dad?

989
01:18:26,068 --> 01:18:27,535
I just don't.

990
01:18:28,037 --> 01:18:30,232
Why don't you want to see him?

991
01:18:30,906 --> 01:18:32,066
He's your dad.

992
01:18:32,808 --> 01:18:35,011
Don't be naughty.

993
01:18:35,011 --> 01:18:37,646
Yang Yang doesn't want to go.

994
01:18:37,646 --> 01:18:39,546
You must do as we say.

995
01:18:39,982 --> 01:18:41,083
I will not go.

996
01:18:41,083 --> 01:18:42,251
Why not?

997
01:18:42,251 --> 01:18:43,183
Tell me.

998
01:18:43,953 --> 01:18:46,183
Could I speak with the Chief?

999
01:18:47,089 --> 01:18:49,683
Chief, could you please come here?

1000
01:18:54,063 --> 01:18:55,587
Let's talk over there.

1001
01:18:57,633 --> 01:18:59,328
Don't cry Yang Yang.

1002
01:19:00,036 --> 01:19:01,670
We are not going.

1003
01:19:01,670 --> 01:19:02,534
Don't cry.

1004
01:19:12,782 --> 01:19:14,215
Chief

1005
01:19:15,317 --> 01:19:16,284
everyone

1006
01:19:18,888 --> 01:19:20,719
I'm sorry for causing you any trouble.

1007
01:19:22,725 --> 01:19:28,925
I've decided not to take Yang Yang to the prison.

1008
01:19:30,132 --> 01:19:31,724
Yang Yang

1009
01:19:35,838 --> 01:19:38,363
might not be ready

1010
01:19:40,643 --> 01:19:43,578
to meet his father yet.

1011
01:19:45,214 --> 01:19:47,239
Although he is just a child

1012
01:19:50,352 --> 01:19:52,616
I think we should try to understand

1013
01:19:54,790 --> 01:19:58,191
and respect his wishes on this.

1014
01:20:15,945 --> 01:20:17,713
All right.

1015
01:20:17,713 --> 01:20:19,010
Yang Yang will not go.

1016
01:20:28,657 --> 01:20:32,388
Who will raise Yang Yang now?

1017
01:20:35,264 --> 01:20:36,699
Tell him not to worry.

1018
01:20:36,699 --> 01:20:38,291
The village will keep caring for Yang Yang.

1019
01:20:38,767 --> 01:20:41,235
Li will be released in 2 years.

1020
01:20:41,871 --> 01:20:44,173
We'll arrange a meeting then.

1021
01:20:44,173 --> 01:20:46,664
The boy will be united with his dad.

1022
01:20:47,343 --> 01:20:48,901
We will take care of it.

1023
01:21:17,873 --> 01:21:21,673
Jasmine, one moment.

1024
01:23:57,232 --> 01:23:59,097
Yang Yang!

1025
01:24:26,962 --> 01:24:27,963
Mr. Takata

1026
01:24:27,963 --> 01:24:29,988
what do you want to do now?

1027
01:24:31,300 --> 01:24:33,495
I would like to visit the prison again.

1028
01:24:34,870 --> 01:24:37,206
If possible

1029
01:24:37,206 --> 01:24:39,401
I'd still like to film Li's performance.

1030
01:24:42,211 --> 01:24:44,907
Could you contact Warden Chen

1031
01:24:46,181 --> 01:24:49,548
to see if Li would be willing?

1032
01:24:50,352 --> 01:24:54,686
You may have to wait a few days for an answer

1033
01:24:58,327 --> 01:24:59,191
I'll wait.

1034
01:24:59,928 --> 01:25:01,452
All right.

1035
01:25:29,992 --> 01:25:30,981
Father.

1036
01:25:34,496 --> 01:25:35,554
Father

1037
01:25:38,267 --> 01:25:40,997
I've been trying to contact you for hours

1038
01:25:42,504 --> 01:25:45,940
but I couldn't get through.

1039
01:25:50,078 --> 01:25:51,568
Ken-ichi

1040
01:25:56,351 --> 01:25:58,046
passed away

1041
01:26:00,489 --> 01:26:04,391
Last night.

1042
01:26:25,614 --> 01:26:27,741
Yesterday during the day

1043
01:26:29,251 --> 01:26:30,582
Ken-ichi

1044
01:26:31,753 --> 01:26:34,187
was in high spirits.

1045
01:26:36,692 --> 01:26:39,320
He talked about you

1046
01:26:42,097 --> 01:26:45,123
and wanted to write you a letter.

1047
01:26:48,403 --> 01:26:51,429
He spoke. I wrote it down.

1048
01:27:02,451 --> 01:27:07,514
I wrote down...every word he said.

1049
01:27:11,560 --> 01:27:13,653
Shall I read it to you?

1050
01:27:21,670 --> 01:27:25,231
Do you want to listen to it now?

1051
01:27:29,778 --> 01:27:31,712
Please, read it to me Rie.

1052
01:27:42,190 --> 01:27:44,090
What do I want to say?

1053
01:27:45,527 --> 01:27:48,223
What should I say to my father?

1054
01:27:49,464 --> 01:27:52,365
I'm asking myself.

1055
01:27:53,435 --> 01:27:56,838
I deeply regret refusing to see you

1056
01:27:56,838 --> 01:27:59,170
when you came to the hospital.

1057
01:28:00,242 --> 01:28:01,709
This feeling of regret

1058
01:28:03,345 --> 01:28:07,338
torments me more than my illness.

1059
01:28:09,618 --> 01:28:11,279
I've been blaming you

1060
01:28:13,221 --> 01:28:15,280
ever since Mother's death.

1061
01:28:17,092 --> 01:28:19,390
Without any explanation

1062
01:28:20,429 --> 01:28:22,420
you moved away to a remote fishing village.

1063
01:28:25,534 --> 01:28:26,398
I thought then

1064
01:28:27,569 --> 01:28:29,366
you were trying to avoid facing reality.

1065
01:28:30,906 --> 01:28:32,134
To be honest

1066
01:28:33,342 --> 01:28:35,105
I've been trying to escape it as well.

1067
01:28:36,712 --> 01:28:38,737
When you came to the hospital

1068
01:28:39,481 --> 01:28:41,176
I couldn't face the distance between us.

1069
01:28:43,652 --> 01:28:45,483
People have never understood

1070
01:28:46,321 --> 01:28:52,749
my obsession with folk opera.

1071
01:28:53,128 --> 01:28:53,822
I've been drawn to them

1072
01:28:54,763 --> 01:28:56,822
because they mirror my life.

1073
01:28:58,266 --> 01:29:00,496
I've come to realize

1074
01:29:01,536 --> 01:29:02,804
that I'm the actor behind

1075
01:29:02,804 --> 01:29:03,702
the mask.

1076
01:29:06,675 --> 01:29:08,336
I've tried to fool myself

1077
01:29:09,277 --> 01:29:11,142
and everyone close to me.

1078
01:29:12,581 --> 01:29:13,741
My true feelings

1079
01:29:14,383 --> 01:29:16,351
have eluded me until now.

1080
01:29:18,520 --> 01:29:20,613
I have not allowed myself

1081
01:29:23,525 --> 01:29:24,617
to acknowledge them.

1082
01:29:26,361 --> 01:29:27,692
Father,

1083
01:29:28,196 --> 01:29:30,391
it's not the opera that is important.

1084
01:29:31,900 --> 01:29:32,867
I now see

1085
01:29:34,336 --> 01:29:35,671
that loved ones

1086
01:29:35,671 --> 01:29:42,235
should not mask their true feelings for one another

1087
01:29:48,850 --> 01:29:49,942
I eagerly wait for your return.

1088
01:29:51,553 --> 01:29:52,952
Father

1089
01:29:53,355 --> 01:29:55,949
I want us to embrace each other once again.

1090
01:30:54,783 --> 01:30:57,752
Mr. Takata. Lingo.

1091
01:30:58,253 --> 01:30:59,488
Jasmine?

1092
01:30:59,488 --> 01:31:00,689
Hello Warden Chen.

1093
01:31:00,689 --> 01:31:01,781
Mr. Takata.

1094
01:31:01,823 --> 01:31:05,293
I'm sorry that last time

1095
01:31:05,293 --> 01:31:07,262
Li couldn't sing.

1096
01:31:07,262 --> 01:31:09,025
I've organized more people this time

1097
01:31:09,698 --> 01:31:11,700
to create a crowd to cheer him on.

1098
01:31:11,700 --> 01:31:13,565
I hope it will go well today.

1099
01:31:14,069 --> 01:31:15,263
Li.

1100
01:31:15,437 --> 01:31:16,495
Yes, sir.

1101
01:31:16,805 --> 01:31:18,373
Tell Mr. Takata what you want to say.

1102
01:31:18,373 --> 01:31:20,942
Mr. Takata, I'm sorry about last time.

1103
01:31:20,942 --> 01:31:22,432
I'll do my best this time.

1104
01:31:27,349 --> 01:31:28,509
Warden Chen

1105
01:31:30,385 --> 01:31:34,289
thank you for arranging this.

1106
01:31:34,289 --> 01:31:36,280
It's very kind of you.

1107
01:31:37,058 --> 01:31:38,787
Today, however

1108
01:31:40,095 --> 01:31:41,858
I am not here to film the opera.

1109
01:31:43,565 --> 01:31:45,362
I've waited for two days

1110
01:31:46,935 --> 01:31:49,335
just to meet Mr. Li.

1111
01:31:50,305 --> 01:31:53,001
May I have a few words with him?

1112
01:32:06,721 --> 01:32:08,985
Of course.

1113
01:32:17,432 --> 01:32:18,797
Mr. Li

1114
01:32:21,603 --> 01:32:23,366
I've been to Stone Village.

1115
01:32:32,414 --> 01:32:33,847
I've met Yang Yang.

1116
01:32:42,858 --> 01:32:44,689
You saw Yang Yang?

1117
01:32:55,570 --> 01:33:00,564
He is a good boy. He really is.

1118
01:33:19,761 --> 01:33:20,785
Warden Chen

1119
01:33:21,062 --> 01:33:23,465
I've taken some photos of his son.

1120
01:33:23,465 --> 01:33:24,693
May I show him?

1121
01:33:28,503 --> 01:33:29,561
What photos?

1122
01:33:32,674 --> 01:33:35,472
Photos of his son and the village.

1123
01:33:39,014 --> 01:33:40,140
Photos of his son?

1124
01:33:41,182 --> 01:33:44,640
Please show us.

1125
01:35:58,286 --> 01:35:59,617
That's all.

1126
01:36:00,555 --> 01:36:03,251
Sorry these are all I have.

1127
01:36:34,722 --> 01:36:35,950
Li

1128
01:36:36,891 --> 01:36:38,359
Mr. Takata traveled a great distance

1129
01:36:38,359 --> 01:36:40,691
to take these photos for you.

1130
01:36:41,062 --> 01:36:43,231
Your son is a bright boy.

1131
01:36:43,231 --> 01:36:44,632
Everyone would agree with me.

1132
01:36:44,632 --> 01:36:46,293
He is really delightful.

1133
01:36:47,602 --> 01:36:49,194
You should thank Mr. Takata.

1134
01:36:51,306 --> 01:36:53,638
Thank you, Mr. Takata.

1135
01:36:57,846 --> 01:36:59,336
Can you perform?

1136
01:37:00,048 --> 01:37:01,140
I'll sing to the best of my ability.

1137
01:37:08,957 --> 01:37:10,891
There is really no need to perform.

1138
01:37:11,860 --> 01:37:13,725
I didn't come to film the opera today.

1139
01:37:18,266 --> 01:37:19,096
Mr. Takata

1140
01:37:19,934 --> 01:37:21,369
I've arranged the band

1141
01:37:21,369 --> 01:37:22,704
and the crowd.

1142
01:37:22,704 --> 01:37:24,239
A lot of men in our region

1143
01:37:24,239 --> 01:37:26,107
can sing mask opera.

1144
01:37:26,107 --> 01:37:28,309
I've picked some good ones

1145
01:37:28,309 --> 01:37:29,310
to accompany him.

1146
01:37:29,310 --> 01:37:31,778
I hope you stay for the opera.

1147
01:37:39,854 --> 01:37:42,015
There's really no need for me to film it.

1148
01:37:44,826 --> 01:37:46,060
Let me put it this way.

1149
01:37:46,060 --> 01:37:47,925
You don't have to film it.

1150
01:37:48,696 --> 01:37:50,254
We invite you to be our audience.

1151
01:37:50,832 --> 01:37:53,101
We'll perform the opera.

1152
01:37:53,101 --> 01:37:55,467
Please, will you sit here and watch?

1153
01:38:43,952 --> 01:38:45,510
Mr. Takata

1154
01:38:46,020 --> 01:38:47,112
thank you.

